1-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adventistreview.org/1803-20|title= Beginning in Battle Creek|website=Adventist Review|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wmuk.org/post/federal-center-housed-famous-americans-army-hospital-sanitarium|title=Federal Center Housed Famous Americans as Army Hospital, Sanitarium|website=Western Michigan University|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n* Benghazi Adventist Hospital - (closed by the military government), Benghazi, Libya<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.eud.adventist.org/en/all-commentaries/commentary/go/-/may-21-in-the-adventist-history/|title=May 21 in the Adventist History|website=Inter-European Division|access-date=2019-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.blacksdahistory.org/Gadaffi_and_Adventism.html|title=Muammar Gaddafi and Seventh-day Adventism|website=blacksdahistory.org|access-date=2019-02-27}}</ref>\n* [[Boston Regional Medical Center]] - (formerly New England Sanitarium and Hospital; also New England Memorial Hospital), (sold to Gutierrez Company), Stoneham, Massachusetts, United States<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adventistreview.org/1803-22|title=The Enduring Light in Massachusetts|website=Adventist Review|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://homenewshere.com/middlesex_east/article_8f45e090-0dc2-11e8-a171-07f79f01954d.html|title=Developers break ground at Boston Regional Medical Center|website=Woburn Daily Times|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref>\n* Chongchen Hospital - (closed by the [[Communists]]), China<ref name=closed>{{Cite web|url=http://www.adventisminchina.org/department/health|title=Health|website=Adventism in China|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref>\n* Florida Hospital Oceanside (Damaged by [[Hurricane Irma]] and years later AdventHealth had it [[Demolition|demolished]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news-journalonline.com/news/20181230/florida-hospital-oceanside-in-ormond-prepares-for-demolition|title=Florida Hospital Oceanside in Ormond prepares for demolition|last=Ross|first=Nikki|date=2018-12-30|website=The Daytona Beach News-Journal|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n* Fushan Hospital - (closed by the Communists), China<ref name=closed/>\n* Guangzhou Sanitarium - (closed by the Communists), Guangzhou, China<ref name=closed/>\n* Henan Hospital - (closed by the Communists), China<ref name=closed/>\n* [[Jellico Community Hospital]] - (formerly operated by [[AdventHealth|Adventist Health System]]), Jellico, Tennessee<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsjournal.net/adventist-health-system-to-cease-operating-jellico-community-hospital/|title=Adventist Health System to cease operating Jellico Community Hospital|website=The News Journal|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref>\n* Knowlton Sanitarium - (sold), [[Brome Lake, Quebec|Knowlton, Quebec]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://adventisthistory.wordpress.com/2008/10/19/knowlton-sanitarium-quebec-1903-1908/|title=Knowlton Sanitarium, Quebec, 1903-1908|website=Adventist History Library|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pressreader.com/canada/sherbrooke-record/20190813/281732681120557|title=The history of the Knowlton Sanitarium|website=Pressreader|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref>\n* Kondeng Hospital - (closed by the Communists), China<ref name=closed/>\n* McClelan Memorial Hospital - (closed or sold), [[Riverside-Albert, New Brunswick|Riverside, New Brunswick]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://adventisthistory.wordpress.com/2008/10/21/mcclelan-memorial-hospital-1953/|title=McClelan Memorial Hospital, 1953|website=Adventist History Library|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref>\n* Naning Hospital - (closed by the Communists), China<ref name=closed/>\n* North China Sanitarium - (closed by the Communists), China<ref name=closed/>\n* Northwest Sanitarium - (closed by the Communists), China<ref name=closed/>\n* North York Branson Hospital - (sold to [[North York General Hospital]] and renamed Branson Ambulatory Care Centre), Toronto, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.toronto.com/news-story/7176821-north-york-general-hospital-closing-branson-ambulatory-care-centre/|title=North York General Hospital closing Branson Ambulatory Care Centre|website=North York Mirror|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref>\n* [[Paradise Valley Hospital California|Paradise Valley Hospital]] - (formerly Mount Paradise Sanitarium; Potts Sanitarium; Paradise Sanitarium; Paradise Valley Saniatarium & Paradise Valley Sanitarium, School of Nursing)(sold to [[Prime Healthcare Services]]), National City, California, United States<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sandiegohistory.org/journal/1989/april/hospital/|title=Hospital Based Nursing Schools in San Diego, 1900-1970|website=San Diego History Center|access-date=2019-05-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.modernhealthcare.com/article/20141129/MAGAZINE/311299987/the-man-behind-the-nation-s-fastest-growing-hospital-chain|title=The man behind the nation's fastest-growing hospital chain|website=Modern Healthcare|access-date=2019-05-24}}</ref> \n* Rangoon Seventh-day Adventist Hospital - (closed by the military gorvernment, currently [[Yangon ENT Hospital]], Yangoon, Myanmar<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eyemyanmar.com/yangon-eye-hospital-2/|title=Yangon Eye Hospital|website=EyeMyanmar|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=G9T-CgAAQBAJ&pg=PA215&lpg=PA215&dq=Rangoon+Seventh-day+Adventist+Hospital&source=bl&ots=3xifyHPvio&sig=ACfU3U0voGUC8oZbq42thq9ui2PdwukrZQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwil5MS35JviAhVO...|title=A Delicate Relationship:The United States and Burma/ Myanmar Since 1945|website= Google|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref>\n* Rest Haven Hospital & Sanitarium - (moved from an island to the mainland and is now operated as Rest Haven Lodge a retirement facility), Sydney, British Columbia, Canada<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.adventisthealth.ca/rest-haven-lodge/|title=Rest Haven Lodge|website=Caltca|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://digital.lib.sfu.ca/bcp-9088/lounge-rest-haven-hospital-sanitarium-sidney-vi-bc |title=The Lounge Rest Haven Hospital & Sanitarium Sidney, V.I. B.C.|website=Simon Fraser University|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://digital.lib.sfu.ca/bcp-9091/rest-haven-hospital-and-sanitarium-sidney-vi-bc|title=Rest Haven Hospital and Sanitarium, Sidney (V.I.) B.C.|website=Simon Fraser University|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref> \n* [[Saigon Adventist Hospital]] - (closed by the Communists and know owned by Ph\u00fa Nhuan\u00e2n Red Cross Association), Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.historicvietnam.com/former-saigon-adventist-hospital/|title=Old Saigon Building of the Week-Former Saigon Adventist Hospital, 1961|website=Historic Vietnam|access-date=2019-05-03}}</ref> \n* Shanghai Sanitarium - (closed by the Communists), Shanghai, China<ref name=closed/>\n* Shenyang Sanitarium - (closed by the Communists), Shenyang, China<ref name=closed/>\n* Skodsbog Sanitarium - (sold to [[Augustinus Foundation]], currently it goes by the name [[Skodsborg Spa Hotel]]), Skodsbog, Denmark<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ministrymagazine.org/archive/1948/09/the-health-work-in-scandinavia|title=The Health Work in Scandinavia|website=Ministry Magazine|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.healthista.com/spa-review-kurhotel-skodsborg-copenhagen/|title=Spa review:Kurhotel Skodsborg, Copenhagen|website=Healthista|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref>\n* Taishan Hospital - (closed by the Communists and renamed [[Taishan City People's Hospital]]), Taishan, China<ref name=closed/>\n* Tempe Community Hospital - (sold by [[Adventist Health]] to [[Iasis Healthcare]] then renamed [[Tempe St. Luke's Hospital]]), Tempe, Arizona<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/books/politics-and-business-magazines/adventist-health|title=Adventist Health|website=Encyclopedia.com|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wranglernews.com/2017/10/10/tempe-st-lukes-join-largest-u-s-private-hospital-network/|title= Tempe St. Luke's to join largest U.S. private-hospital network|website=Wrangler News|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nashvillepost.com/business/health-care/article/20862066/cerberusbacked-company-buying-iasis-operations|title=Cerberus-backed company buying Iasis|website=NashvillePost|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref>\n* [[Walla Walla General Hospital]] - (closed by [[Adventist Health]]), Walla Walla, Washington, United States<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcrightnow.com/archives/walla-walla-general-hospital-closes-its-doors/article_d9dc16ea-4f72-5586-9bb2-b89bdd97fc58.html|title= Walla Walla General Hospital closes its doors|website=NBC Right Now|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.healthcarefinancenews.com/news/adventist-health-closes-walla-walla-general-hospital-under-strain-mounting-financial-issues|title=Adventist Health closes Walla Walla General Hospital|website=Healthcare Finance|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref>\n* [[Warburton Hospital]] - (sold), Warburton, Australia{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n* Wei Chou Hospital - (closed by the Communists), China<ref name=closed/>\n* Wuhan Sanitarium - (closed by the Communists), Wuhan, China<ref name=closed/>\n* Youngberg Memorial Adventist Hospital - (closed and was bought by the [[Salvation Army]] and turned into a [[Charity shop|thrift store]]), Singapore<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://roots.sg/learn/collections/listing/1211999|title= The Youngberg Memorial Adventist Hospital at Upper Serangoon Road|website=Roots|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Seventh-day Adventist colleges and universities]]\n*[[List of Seventh-day Adventist secondary schools]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.adventistdirectory.org/ Adventist Directory] Locate Adventist Entities\n*[http://www.adventistyearbook.org/ Adventist Yearbook] The Official Organizational Directory\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Seventh-Day Adventist Hospitals}}\n[[Category:Lists of hospitals|Seventh-day Adventist]]\n[[Category:Hospitals affiliated with the Seventh-day Adventist Church| List]]\n[[Category:Seventh-day Adventist Church-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{More citations needed|date=August 2018}}\n{{Seventh-day Adventism}}\nThe following is a list of [[Seventh-day Adventist Church|Seventh-day Adventist]] hospitals.\n\n==[[North American Division of Seventh-day Adventists|North American Division]]==\n\n[[Adventist Health]]\n* Adventist Health Bakersfield, [[Bakersfield, California]], (formerly named San Joaquin Community Hospital)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakersfield.com/news/san-joaquin-community-hospital-announces-new-name-mission/article_2b993171-3aaf-5486-8fbb-b0b4b8fc9cd5.html|title=San Joaquin Community Hospital announces new name, mission|website=The Bakersfield Californian|access-date=May 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakersfield.com/news/health/adventist-health-bakersfield-shutters-burn-center-citing-competition/article_6c97eb32-c41c-11e7-91ae-9780ca1fd548.html|title=Adventist Health Bakersfield shutters burn center citing competition|website=The Bakersfield Californian|access-date=May 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakersfield.com/news/health/hats-off-for-heart-health-awareness-at-adventist-health-bakersfield/article_dede2aa0-11bd-11e8-bae9-633b5bafd13c.html|title=Hats off for heart health awareness at Adventist Health Bakersfield's NICU|website=The Bakersfield Californian|access-date=May 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakersfield.com/news/adventist-health-bakersfield-receives-major-industry-award/article_5751e4cc-fca5-11e8-9f4b-73ef5ce6696f.html|title=Adventist Health Bakersfield receives major industry award|website=The Bakersfield Californian|access-date=May 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakersfield.com/kern-business-journal/adventist-healt